    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - KINGPIN BUSHING AND SEAL REPLACEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>KINGPIN BUSHING AND SEAL REPLACEMENT</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove grease seals from knuckle arms using a suitable tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drive bushings out of knuckles using a suitable piloted drift (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200711">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200711" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200711" filename="../figg02/G0200711.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Using a Piloted Drift</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all foreign material from kingpin areas of steering knuckle and axle beam.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wire brush machined surfaces taking care not to damage them. Clean kingpin bores (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200712">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200712" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200712" filename="../figg02/G0200712.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Clean Kingpin Bores</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
